{"build_type":"library","description":"SIGTRAP single-step handler (TRACE-REPLAY DEBUGGER): on each single-step trap it calls the single trace writer to record the full machine state, then re-arms the trap flag (EFLAGS bit 0x100 at ucontext+176) while the trace ring has room, clearing it once the ring is full to bound the trace. The trap delivery is the thin Linux signal driver (swappable to a #DB IDT handler on bare metal); the logic above is Linux-agnostic.","module_name":"record-single-step-trap-appending-trace-ring","package_name":"record-single-step-trap-appending-trace-ring","function_definitions":{"record-single-step-trap-appending-trace-ring":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"signum","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"siginfo","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"ucontext","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"tbase","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":106652627894272},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"cap","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16384},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"efoff","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":176},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"tf","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":256},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"notf","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":-257},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"append-trace-step-into-ring-buffer","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"ucontext"}],"result_assignment_variable":"_w","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"array_read","bas